definition.value: An organyl group consisting of a benzene ring with three nitro substituents at positions 2, 4 and 6 relative to the point of attachment.
The arenesulfonate oxoanion that is benzenesulfonate anion with two nitro substituents in the 2- and 4-positions.
The arenesulfonic acid that is benzenesulfonic acid with two nitro substituents in the 2- and 4-positions.
A galactonate that is the conjugate base of L-galactonic acid.
A L-galactose 1-phosphate compound having beta-configuration about the anomeric centre.
A cyclopropenone compound having phenyl substituents at the 2- and 3-positions.
Three-membered alicyclic ketones containing a single C=C double bond.

A 1,3-oxazole compound having a phenyl substituent at the 2-position, an ethoxymethylene group at the 4-position, and an oxo group at the 5-position.  It is a chemical allergen used for immunological experiments, particularly for experiments on delayed type hypersensitivity.
A monocarboxylic acid amide  having an N-(5-carboxypentyl) substituent and a C-(4-hydroxy-3-nitrophenyl) substituent.
A lysine derivative having a 2,4-dinitrophenyl substituent at the N(6)-position.

An amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of lysine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of lysine by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing lysine residues.
The L-stereoisomer of N(6)-(2,4-dinitrophenyl)lysine, a lysine derivative having a 2,4-dinitrophenyl substituent at the N(6)-position.
An N-acylethanolamine compound formed by a condensation of prostaglandin F2alpha and ethanolamine.
An N-acylethanolamine compound formed by a condensation of prostaglandin H2 and ethanolamine.
A serine derivative having a 2,4-dinitrophenyl substituent on nitrogen.
The L-stereoisomer of N-(2,4-dinitrophenyl)serine, an L-serine derivative having a 2,4-dinitrophenyl) substituent on nitrogen.
A proline derivative having a 2,4-dinitrophenyl substituent on nitrogen.
The L-stereoisomer of N-(2,4-dinitrophenyl)proline, a proline derivative having a 2,4-dinitrophenyl substituent on nitrogen.
A carboxamide compound having an N-(5-carboxypentyl) substituent and a C-(4-hydroxy--5-iodo-3-nitrophenyl) substituent.
A dihydroxyanthraquinone compound in which the hydroxy groups are at C-1 and C-2 and which has a bis[(carboxymethyl)amino]methyl substituent at the 3-position.
A 1-hydroxyanthraquinone compound having a carboxy substituent at the 2-position and a bromo substituent at the 4-position.
A carbodiimide compound having a cyclohexyl substituent on both nitrogen atoms.
Any organonitrogen compound that consists of two primary amino groups joined to a central carbon atom via N=C linkages.
A carbodiimide compound having an isopropyl substituent on both nitrogen atoms.
A carbodiimide compound having a 4-methylphenyl substituent on both nitrogen atoms.
An imidazoline compound having the double bond at the 2-position.
Diazoline compounds having the nitrogen atoms at the 1- and 3-positions and a double bond at an unspecified position.
A linear-fused organic heterotetracyclic compound consisting of a [1,3,2]dioxaphosphinane fused to a pyran ring which is in turn fused to a pteridine ring system.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a adenylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a deoxyadenylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a guanylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a deoxyguanylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a thymidylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a cytidylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 5'-end bound-monomer of a deoxycytidylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a uridylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
An aflatoxin B1 compound formed via enzymic epoxidation of aflatoxin B1 followed by non-enzymic hydrolysis.
A 1,4-dialdehyde compound having a hydroxy substituent at the 2-position and a 7-hydroxy-9-methoxy-3,4-dioxo-1,4-dihydro-3H-furo[3,4-c]chromen-6-yl group at the 3-position.
An organic heterotricyclic compound obtained by oxidative cleavage of the furofuran ring system of aflatoxin B1.
A quinone imine having amino substituents in the 2- and 5-positions and 4-aminophenyl substituents on both of the imine nitrogens. It is a trimer formed from 1,4-phenylenediamine.
Phthalimide substituted at the 4- and 5-positions by anilino groups.
A beta-D-glucoside compound having 3-acetyl-7-hydroxycoumarin as the anomeric substituent.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a adenylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a deoxyadenylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a guanylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
Caffeine substituted at its 8-position by an (E)-3-chlorostyryl group.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a cytidylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a deoxyguanylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
The 3'-end bound-monomer of a thymidylyl-5'-monophosphoric acid that is part of a nucleic acid.
